## Configuration

Way-of-working choices live in `.workbench/config.json`. Files generated by workbench are recorded in `.workbench/manifest.json`; run `/workbench:upgrade` to reconcile them after a plugin update. Edit this file freely — it is a `merge` file, so `/workbench:upgrade` preserves your changes.

## Compact Instructions

When compacting this conversation, ALWAYS preserve: the loop charter — goal + hard constraints (`.workbench/loop-charter.md`); the current `in-development/` task IDs and owners; the last commit SHA per repo; the `in-review` count vs cap; any open `decisions/`; and the `/workbench:loop` resume command. Drop verbose tool output and resolved side-quests first. The charter and `.claude/SESSION_STATE.md` live on disk — re-read them rather than trusting summarized memory.
